On Abandoning Rails

Programming is beautiful because it is simple. There are these rules, these tiny rules that you can hold in your head. And then you zoom out, and make rules out of these rules, and then make rules out of those, and finally you have this amazing, delicate structure that is inevitable and exquisite. Most people who really get hooked on programming for themselves seem to do it for web development, ormaking a tool. I did it for solving Project Euler problems.

